century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Trye Jr. was born in 1468, in Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Trye, was 34 and his mother, Isabel Berkeley, was 32. He married Anne Baynham about 1484, in Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1524, in Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 56, and was buried in Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England."},"et":{"1468–1524":"1468–1524","1470–1535":"1470–1535","1484–1526":"1484–1526","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1437–1498":"1437–1498","1484":"1484","1470":"1470","6 December 1497":"6. detsember 1497","1437":"1437","1524":"1524","1535":"1535","1468":"1468","1435":"1435","Abt 1465":"umbes 1465","1498":"1498","1497":"1497","about 1484":"umbes 1484","1526":"1526","Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England","Hardwicke and Redwick, Gloucester, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hardwicke,Gloucestershire, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"1468–1524":"1468–1524","1470–1535":"1470–1535","1484–1526":"1484–1526","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1437–1498":"1437–1498","1484":"1484","1470":"1470","6 December 1497":"6. joulukuuta 1497","1437":"1437","1524":"1524","1535":"1535","1468":"1468","1435":"1435","Abt 1465":"noin 1465","1498":"1498","1497":"1497","about 1484":"noin 1484","1526":"1526","Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England","Hardwicke and Redwick, Gloucester, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunt